title: For Trade:  Italian Military Police Beretta 92s
postcontent: This is Italian police Beretta 92s. This particular pistol has matching numbers and in excellent mechanical condition and decent cosmetic condition. The frame and slide has some holster wear and some small cosmetic wear as this was issued for duty in Italian police and military forces throughout the 70s and 80s. The original magazine works perfectly and has no issues locking the slide open (some older 92s mags have an issue with weak springs). This pistol has some expensive new imported wooden grips installed. Its very difficult to find fitting grips for this pistol. There are a few differences from its younger sibling the 92fs. Notice the European heel mag release instead of the standard mag release. Also the magazines have a small cutout near the bottom to properly lock in this pistol. The good news is that most official Beretta 92fs magazines still come with this notch.This pistol comes with a soft pistol case, the original 15 round Italian Magazine, a new 17 round promag brand magazine, the original plastic grips with the original screws.I recently found the period correct military holster with the belt. I added a picture for reference.If ad is still up I still have the pistol.

title: For Sale:  Preban Daewoo Max II 5.56mm folding stock Rifle
postcontent: This is a pretty rare one. The South Korean license for Daewoo to produce the Colt M16 expired in 1984. Also, the Koreans were expressly prohibited from exporting/selling license built Colts. To alleviate that, the South Koreans initiated the XB rifle program in 1972 to develop a Korean designed and built successor. The result in 1983 was the adoption of the Daewoo K2 5.56mm assault rifle. It is still their standard military issued rifle today. Daewoo exported a few semi-auto versions of the rifle both before the 1989 Bush import ban and after. This Max II is one of the preban import guns featuring their unique long stroke gas piston/recoil spring setup (similar to an AK) and FAL style gas plug and hinged upper. It features a side folding stock. It is chambered in 5.56mm with a 1/7 twist barrel and uses M16/AR15 magazines. This rifle is one of those preban guns imported by Stoeger (post-ban guns were imported by Kimber and cannot take the side folding stock). My price is $1500. I'm looking to sell because I keep buying too many Colt and S&W pre-1982 revolvers. If you have some of those that I don't have (or a 1970's Colt Combat Commander) we might talk trades. This rifle will come with the sling and a USGI Adventure Line Vietnam era 20 round mag.I need to do a FTF in the North Dallas area (I am in Plano). First to say they take it (or arrange a trade), gets it. I do have it cross listed. I can be reached via email thru Armslist or text me at 214 - 471 - 79four1
